NESS began life at the end of 2011 in order to build ideas about new ways of thinking regarding how the economy and society operate.<br>NESS is holding a one day policy-oriented conference in London on 28th October, where we will be drawing out practical implications in key areas such as: [...]    </description>   <dc:date>2014-09-15T19:32:10+02:00</dc:date>   <dc:creator>Greg Fisher</dc:creator>   <dc:identifier>https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk:443/cgi-bin/webadmin?A2=COMPLEXITY;86d9deb9.1409</dc:identifier> </item>  <item rdf:about="https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk:443/cgi-bin/webadmin?A2=COMPLEXITY;f5288bd8.1408">   <title>Call for Participation: Policy Modelling Workshop. Models of institutions in the existing literature mainly focused on common-pool resources and generally took institutions as rules. At the same time, due to conceptual connections between the second and third types of institutions, some [...]    </description>   <dc:date>2014-06-04T15:08:34+00:00</dc:date>   <dc:creator>Ozge Dilaver</dc:creator>   <dc:identifier>https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk:443/cgi-bin/webadmin?A2=COMPLEXITY;9df008b3.1406</dc:identifier> </item>  <item rdf:about="https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk:443/cgi-bin/webadmin?A2=COMPLEXITY;b8740bbf.1406">   <title>Role of Social Media in Science Policy? - Guardian Blog Event </title>   <link>https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk:443/cgi-bin/webadmin?A2=COMPLEXITY;b8740bbf.1406</link>   <description> List members might be interested in this event. Please complete this survey about our online engagement. The outcome will help the four projects with their remaining activities and inform future initiatives.<br><br>The survey will close on Monday 9th June 2014.<br><br>https://www.surveymonkey.com/s/RSDLHS6<br><br>Thanks very much<br><br>Alison Cooper<br>Complexity Science for the Real World Coordinator   </description>   <dc:date>2014-06-03T08:42:26+01:00</dc:date>   <dc:creator>Alison Cooper</dc:creator>   <dc:identifier>https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk:443/cgi-bin/webadmin?A2=COMPLEXITY;87ae4fe0.1406</dc:identifier> </item>  <item rdf:about="https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk:443/cgi-bin/webadmin?A2=COMPLEXITY;9ad59cc0.1405">   <title>Sub list for those around manchester </title>   <link>https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk:443/cgi-bin/webadmin?A2=COMPLEXITY;9ad59cc0.1405</link>   <description> If you live near enough manchester there is another JISC list called<br>manchester-complexity@jiscmail.ac.uk for complexity notices/events relevant<br>to complexity science in manchester.<br><br>To subscribe or look at archives see:<br>http://jiscmail.ac.uk/manchester-complexity<br><br>Regards.   </description>   <dc:date>2014-05-16T13:42:48+01:00</dc:date>   <dc:creator>Bruce Edmonds</dc:creator>   <dc:identifier>https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk:443/cgi-bin/webadmin?A2=COMPLEXITY;9ad59cc0.1405</dc:identifier> </item>  <item rdf:about="https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk:443/cgi-bin/webadmin?A2=COMPLEXITY;6278234a.1405">   <title>Workshop on use of probabilistic forecasts - Royal Statistical Society - 19 June 2014 </title>   <link>https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk:443/cgi-bin/webadmin?A2=COMPLEXITY;6278234a.1405</link>   <description> The main aim of the workshop is to bring together both academics and practitioners of probabilistic population forecasting to discuss barriers to the uses of probabilistic forecasts and possible ways to overcome them. A second aim is to learn from the best practice in other areas of application of probabilistic forecasting.
